## 1. PRE-CONDITIONS

### 1.1 Source reconciliation summary

After reading the Canonical Corpus v10, three things became clear that simplify Thread 17's framing:

1. **The Corpus and the v2.8 plan agree on architecture more than Thread 17 estimated.** The Corpus describes Three-Bucket Wallet (Promotional Bonus → Membership Allocation → Purchased Tokens), append-only ledger, processor abstraction, and advisory-only AI in the same terms the plan uses (where the plan uses them at all). Where Thread 17 saw vocabulary mismatch, much of it dissolves once the Corpus is read.
2. **The Corpus is silent on most plan-named IP assets.** RedBook, GateGuard Sentinel, Cyrano, MyCrew.Zone, CreatorControl.Zone, Diamond Concierge, Welfare Guardian Score, Room-Heat Engine, NOWPayouts, JuryPulse — none appear in the Corpus. They are net-new requirements introduced by the v2.8 plan.
3. **The Corpus is the operational/compliance spine. The plan is the commercial/feature spec.** They are not competing; they are layered. The Corpus says HOW the platform must behave under any feature; the plan says WHICH features. The build implements a subset of both.

This reframes the headline finding: the deficit is not "plan and build are different projects." The deficit is **"the build delivers the Corpus's L0 ship-gate spine but has not yet built the plan's commercial IP layer."**

### 1.2 Repo's eight services map to Corpus L0, not to plan IP

The eight services in the previous OQMI doctrine §8 priority order map cleanly to Corpus L0 ship-gate requirements:

| Repo service | Corpus L0 requirement |
|---|---|
| Three-Bucket Wallet | Ch.1 §4, Ch.7 §5 |
| Risk Engine | Ch.1 §10, Ch.3 §6, Ch.7 §11 |
| NATS Fabric | Ch.7 §3 (event-driven architecture) |
| OBS Broadcast Kernel | Ch.7 §3 (event emission), plan-extension |
| HeartZone IoT Loop | Plan-extension; Corpus silent |
| Bijou.Zone Theatre | Plan-extension; Corpus silent on theatre architecture specifically |
| Sovereign CaC | Ch.3 §3, §4, Ch.6 §4 (compliance gates) |
| UI / Black-Glass Interface | Ch.6 §3 (visual identity) |

Plan IP (RedBook, GateGuard Sentinel, Cyrano, etc.) sits in a layer above this spine. The deficit doc enumerates that layer.

